 to get to that point. Then the article throws out the deja vu concept entirely to mash up alternate dimensions, antimemetics, and fake data glitching with over-the-top lines like ALL TH0SE D3ATH5 F0R N.THI1NgG (leetspeak should also be left in the past) to create buildup that has no mood, atmosphere, or tension. The ending is a confusing, disjointed exposition dump about evil Overseers and multiverse genocide that has zero weight or catharsis and feels utterly disjointed from the rest of the article.

